        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Do GBP posts help with local SEO rankings?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">Yes. Consistent posting signals active profile management and correlates with higher local pack visibility, particularly when posts include keywords, images, and CTAs. Google has confirmed that profile activity is a local ranking factor.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">What types of posts can I publish to GBP?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">Four types are supported: Updates (general announcements), Offers (promotions with dates and optional coupon codes), Events (time-bound happenings), and Product posts (specific items or services). Most tools support Updates; fewer support Offers and Events with full fields.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Can I schedule GBP posts in advance?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">Yes, with the right tools. Publer, SocialBee, Sendible, OneUp, Circleboom, and Localo all support advance scheduling. theStacc goes further — it creates the posts for you and delivers them on a monthly cadence without you scheduling anything.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Do GBP posts expire?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">Yes. Update posts expire after 6 months. Offer posts expire on their set end date. Event posts expire after the event date passes. This means you need a consistent posting cadence to keep your profile populated with fresh content.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Is it safe to use third-party tools for GBP posting?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">Yes. Google allows third-party tools to access and post to GBP via the Google Business Profile API. Tools like BrightLocal, Publer, and Sendible are officially integrated partners. All tools on this list use the approved API.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
